  "prompt": "What is the meaning of \"Stand Up India\" in the scheme \"Stand Up India, Start Up India\"?",
  "response": "\"Stand Up India\" is a government initiative launched by the Indian government to promote entrepreneurship among underserved segments of the population. Specifically, it focuses on supporting women and members of Scheduled Castes (SC) and Scheduled Tribes (ST). The scheme aims to facilitate bank loans between \u20b910 lakh and \u20b91 crore to at least one SC/ST borrower and one woman borrower per bank branch for setting up a greenfield enterprise in manufacturing, services, or trading sectors.\n\nPrime objectives of the \"Stand Up India\" scheme include:\n\n1. **Encouraging Entrepreneurship:** The scheme seeks to foster a culture of entrepreneurship by providing financial support to segments that have traditionally faced barriers to entry into business.\n2. **Financial Inclusion:** By offering credit facilities to underrepresented groups, the initiative aims to bridge the gap in access to financial resources necessary for starting and growing businesses.\n3. **Economic Empowerment:** It promotes economic empowerment of marginalized communities, helping to integrate them into the broader economic ecosystem and uplift their societal status.\n\nOverall, \"Stand Up India\" represents the government's commitment to inclusive growth by offering opportunities to communities that are often left out of mainstream entrepreneurial ventures.",
